        "answer": "Form U4 (Uniform Application for Securities Industry Registration or Transfer) is used to register individuals with FINRA and other regulators. It collects personal, employment, and disciplinary history. Form U5 (Uniform Termination Notice for Securities Industry Registration) is filed by a firm when a registered representative leaves the firm, whether voluntarily or involuntarily, and discloses the reason for termination. Termination must be reported on Form U5 within 30 days. If a representative returns to the industry, they can be reassociated with a new firm using Form U4, provided it's within 2 years to avoid retaking qualification exams."
