        "answer": "The three stages of money laundering are: (1) Placement – introducing illicit funds into the financial system, often through deposits, purchases, or smurfing; (2) Layering – separating the funds from their origin by moving them through complex transactions to obscure their source, such as wire transfers or shell companies; and (3) Integration – reintroducing the laundered funds into the legitimate economy, making them appear legally earned, typically through investments, property purchases, or business activities."
